display size 160x104


a page looks like this:

    4
    3
    2
    1

it can be written to using page(x, y, h) where h is 1 byte
    aabbccdd
and aa is the color of pixel 1, bb the color of pixel 2, etc.
00  off
01  gray
10  dark gray
11  black

To write a binary literal in C, use
    page(x, y, 0baabbccdd);

Colors in hexadecimal:
0x00 off
0x55 gray
0xAA dark gray
0xFF black
